  "A government agency discovers that fish populations in a major fishing region are declining rapidly. Which professional would they most likely hire to assess the situation and recommend management strategies?": "",
  "Marine archaeologist": "",
  "A fisheries biologist specializes in studying fish populations, their health, and reproductive rates. They can assess why a fish population is declining and recommend management strategies such as catch limits, seasonal closures, or habitat restoration to help populations recover.": "",
  "Scientists have detected unusual chemical changes in water samples near an industrial discharge site along the coast. Which marine career professional would investigate this issue?": "",
  "A marine chemist would analyze the water samples to identify the chemicals present, determine their concentrations, and assess how they might affect water quality and marine life. They have the expertise to detect pollutants and trace their sources.": "",
  "A research team needs to explore a hydrothermal vent system 3,000 meters below the ocean surface. Which team member would be responsible for operating the underwater vehicle used in this exploration?": "",
  "Diving specialist": "",
  "At 3,000 meters depth, human diving is impossible, so a remotely operated vehicle (ROV) is used instead. An ROV pilot would operate the vehicle from a research ship, navigating it through the deep ocean to collect samples and video footage of the hydrothermal vent system.": "",
  "Divers have discovered a sunken 18th-century ship off the coast of Florida. Which marine professional should lead the investigation of this underwater site?": "",
  "Environmental consultant": "",
  "Physical oceanographer": "",
  "A marine archaeologist specializes in investigating underwater historical sites such as shipwrecks. They would carefully excavate and document the site, recover artifacts, and piece together the historical significance of the vessel while preserving the site's integrity.": "",
  "An oil company wants to begin drilling off the coast but must first assess the potential environmental impact on nearby marine habitats. Who should they hire?": "",
  "An environmental consultant would conduct an environmental impact assessment to evaluate how drilling operations might affect marine habitats, species, and water quality. They would provide recommendations for minimizing environmental damage and ensuring regulatory compliance.": "",
  "A new aquarium is opening and needs someone to design the exhibits, maintain proper water conditions, and care for the marine animals. Which professional would fill this role?": "",
  "An aquarist is responsible for maintaining aquarium exhibits, monitoring water quality parameters like temperature and salinity, feeding and caring for marine animals, and sometimes designing new exhibit habitats. They combine animal husbandry skills with marine biology knowledge.": "",
  "A country wants to create new laws to protect endangered sea turtles in its territorial waters. Which marine professional would be most helpful in drafting science-based legislation?": "",
  "A marine policy advisor bridges the gap between marine science and law, using scientific research to draft and recommend legislation. They would analyze data on sea turtle populations, identify threats, and help create policies that effectively protect the species while considering economic factors.": "",
  "A university research team is studying how earthquakes on the ocean floor create tsunamis. They need a specialist who understands underwater geological formations and tectonic activity. Which career fits this need?": "",
  "A marine geologist studies the structure and processes of the ocean floor, including plate tectonics, underwater earthquakes, and volcanic activity. They would be essential for understanding how seismic events on the seafloor generate tsunamis and for mapping fault zones beneath the ocean.": ""
